---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import BookingForm from "../components/BookingForm.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title='Lessons &amp; Pricing: Jonathan Zalzman Guitar Lessons | Suwanee, GA'
	description='Guitar, bass, and ukulele lessons in Suwanee, GA, and online anywhere. $159/month for weekly 30-minute lessons. Free trial. Unlimited makeups. No registration fees.'
	nav='lessons'
	bookHref='#book'
>
<!-- ===================== PAGE HERO ===================== -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="page-hero-inner">
    <div class="crumbs">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span class="sep">/</span>
      <span>Lessons</span>
    </div>
    <div class="page-num"><span class="ix">03</span> Lessons &amp; Pricing</div>
    <h1>Pay for the <em>Lesson.</em><br>Not the <span class="accent">Frills.</span></h1>
    <p class="page-lede">Simple monthly pricing. Free trial. No registration fees. <b>Unlimited makeups</b> with 24-hour notice. Lessons in Suwanee or online, your call.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== PRICING (DARK) ===================== -->
<section class="page-section dark">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-eyebrow"><span class="num" style="background:var(--ember);color:var(--bone)">01</span> Choose a Plan</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:50px">Pick How You Start.</h2>

    <div class="plans-detailed">
      <div class="plan-card">
        <div class="plan-label">// Free Trial</div>
        <div class="plan-amount"><sup>$</sup>0<span class="per"> · one time</span></div>
        <p class="plan-desc">A risk-free 30-minute meeting to see if we're a fit.</p>
        <ul class="plan-features">
          <li>Discuss your goals &amp; favorite music</li>
          <li>Assess your current playing level</li>
          <li>Walk away with a custom roadmap</li>
          <li>Zero commitment afterward</li>
          <li>Available in-person or online</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#book" data-plan="trial" class="btn btn-ghost" style="justify-content:center">Book Trial →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="plan-card feat">
        <div class="plan-label">// Weekly Lessons</div>
        <div class="plan-amount"><sup>$</sup>159<span class="per"> /month</span></div>
        <p class="plan-savings">Save 20% vs. single lessons.</p>
        <p class="plan-desc">Weekly 30-minute lessons. The standard plan most students choose.</p>
        <ul class="plan-features">
          <li>Four 30-minute lessons per month</li>
          <li>In-person in Suwanee or online via video</li>
          <li>Video, audio &amp; sheet music between lessons</li>
          <li>Unlimited makeups (24-hour notice)</li>
          <li>Quarterly student performance opportunities</li>
          <li>15% off accessories at Town Center Music</li>
          <li>No registration fees, no contracts</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#book" data-plan="monthly" class="btn btn-primary" style="justify-content:center">Start Free Trial →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="plan-card">
        <div class="plan-label">// À La Carte</div>
        <!-- TODO(jonathan): confirm à la carte price increase to $50 -->
        <div class="plan-amount"><sup>$</sup>50<span class="per"> /lesson</span></div>
        <p class="plan-desc">Single 30-minute lesson, one at a time. No commitment.</p>
        <ul class="plan-features">
          <li>One 30-minute session, paid as you go</li>
          <li>Great for tune-ups or specific questions</li>
          <li>Audition or recital prep</li>
          <li>In-person or online</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#book" data-plan="alacarte" class="btn btn-ghost" style="justify-content:center">Book One →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top:32px;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.08em;color:rgba(244,239,230,.55);text-align:center">
      ★ Longer lesson formats (45 min, 60 min) available on request. Sibling and bundle discounts available, ask when you book.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== WHAT TO EXPECT ===================== -->
<section class="page-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:var(--ember-deep)"><span class="num" style="background:var(--ember-deep);color:var(--bone)">02</span> What to Expect</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:30px">Inside a Lesson.</h2>
    <p style="max-width:60ch;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(14,11,20,.78);margin:0 0 40px">
      Every student's plan is different, but here's the general flow of what a typical lesson looks like, and what you'll get between them.
    </p>

    <div class="expect-grid">
      <div class="expect-cell">
        <span class="ec-num">// 0–5 MIN</span>
        <h3>Check-In</h3>
        <p>How did practice go? What clicked, what didn't? What do you want to focus on today? No quiz, just a conversation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="expect-cell">
        <span class="ec-num">// 5–15 MIN</span>
        <h3>Technique &amp; Theory</h3>
        <p>A short, focused exercise on whatever skill we're building, picking accuracy, a new scale, a tricky chord change.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="expect-cell">
        <span class="ec-num">// 15–28 MIN</span>
        <h3>Songs &amp; Application</h3>
        <p>The fun part. We work through a song you actually want to play, applying what we just drilled. Real music, every week.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="expect-cell">
        <span class="ec-num">// 28–30 MIN</span>
        <h3>Plan the Week</h3>
        <p>I send you a clear practice plan, what to work on, for how long, and which video/audio resources go with it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:60px;padding:36px;background:var(--ink);color:var(--bone);border-radius:4px">
      <h3 class="between-lessons-heading">// Between Lessons</h3>
      <p style="margin:0 0 14px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(244,239,230,.85);max-width:65ch">
        You'll get access to the lesson management app where I drop video demos of exactly what we covered, audio backing tracks for the songs we're working on, sheet music or tabs in PDF, and a structured practice plan you can check off through the week.
      </p>
      <p style="margin:0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(244,239,230,.85);max-width:65ch">
        You can message me with questions any time. If something's not clicking on Tuesday, you don't have to wait until next Saturday's lesson to ask.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== SCHEDULING / FORMAT (TINTED) ===================== -->
<section class="page-section tinted">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="split">
      <div class="split-block">
        <p class="split-eyebrow">// In-Person Lessons</p>
        <h2>Suwanee, GA &amp; Surrounding Areas.</h2>
        <p>I teach in person in Suwanee, convenient to <b>Sugar Hill, Buford, Duluth, John's Creek, Lawrenceville, and Cumming</b>. Easy parking, dedicated lesson space, no waiting in a music-store showroom.</p>
        <p>If you're in Gwinnett County or northern Fulton, in-person is usually the better experience, especially for younger students or absolute beginners. There's no substitute for being able to watch your hands and adjust on the spot.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="split-block">
        <p class="split-eyebrow">// Online Lessons</p>
        <h2>Anywhere With a Camera.</h2>
        <p>Online students get the same plan, the same materials, and the same teacher, just over video. Works great for students <b>outside the Atlanta area</b>, busy adults whose schedules can't handle the drive, traveling families, and college students home for breaks.</p>
        <p>Some students do a hybrid, in-person most weeks, online when life gets busy. Totally fine, totally normal.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== GEAR GUIDE (DARK) ===================== -->
<section class="page-section dark">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-eyebrow"><span class="num" style="background:var(--ember);color:var(--bone)">03</span> Before Your First Lesson</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:30px">What You'll Need.</h2>
    <p style="max-width:60ch;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(244,239,230,.75);margin:0 0 20px">
      Don't go gear shopping before our first lesson. <b>Seriously, wait.</b> A lot of beginners buy the wrong setup based on bad internet advice. Better to have a 15-minute conversation first.
    </p>
    <p style="max-width:60ch;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(244,239,230,.75);margin:0 0 30px">
      That said, here's what you'll generally need to get started:
    </p>

    <div class="gear-list">
      <div class="gear-item">
        <span class="gear-tag">Required</span>
        <h3>An Instrument</h3>
        <p>Any reasonable acoustic, electric, bass, or ukulele works to start. If you're buying one, ask me first, I'll send a few specific recommendations at your budget. No need to spend big.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gear-item">
        <span class="gear-tag">Required</span>
        <h3>A Tuner</h3>
        <p>A clip-on tuner ($15–$20) or a free tuner app on your phone. Playing in tune is non-negotiable, even from lesson one.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gear-item">
        <span class="gear-tag">Helpful</span>
        <h3>Picks &amp; a Strap</h3>
        <p>A pack of medium picks (.73mm is a great starting point) and a strap if you're playing standing up. Total cost: about $10.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gear-item">
        <span class="gear-tag">Electric Only</span>
        <h3>A Small Amp &amp; Cable</h3>
        <p>For electric guitar/bass: any small practice amp (10–20 watts is plenty) and a quarter-inch cable. Headphone amps are a great option if neighbors are a concern.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gear-item">
        <span class="gear-tag">Online Only</span>
        <h3>Webcam &amp; Mic</h3>
        <p>For online lessons: a laptop with a built-in camera works fine to start. We can upgrade your setup later if you stick with it. Decent internet matters more than pro audio gear.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gear-item">
        <span class="gear-tag">Universal</span>
        <h3>Patience &amp; 15 Minutes a Day</h3>
        <p>The biggest predictor of student progress isn't talent or gear, it's consistency. Fifteen minutes daily beats two hours on Sunday every single time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== BOOKING / CONTACT ===================== -->
<section class="page-section" id="book">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:var(--ember-deep)"><span class="num" style="background:var(--ember-deep);color:var(--bone)">04</span> Get Started</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:30px">Book Your Free Lesson.</h2>
    <p style="max-width:60ch;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(14,11,20,.78);margin:0 0 36px">
      Fill this out and I'll be in touch to set up your free 30-minute trial. The first lesson is free, and there's no obligation after.
    </p>

    <BookingForm />

    <div class="contact-alt">
      <p class="contact-alt-head">// Prefer to just call or email?</p>
      <div class="contact-alt-row">
        <a href="tel:7708317936">Call (770) 831-7936</a>
        <span class="sep">·</span>
        <a href="mailto:lessons@jonathanzalzman.com">lessons@jonathanzalzman.com</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
